### JavaScript Carousel Logic (`script.js`)
To implement the functionality to move the carousel left and right, add the following basic JavaScript code in a `script.js` file:

```javascript
let currentSlide = 0;

function moveCarousel(direction) {
    const slides = document.querySelectorAll('.carousel-item');
    const totalSlides = slides.length;

    // Update the current slide index
    currentSlide = (currentSlide + direction + totalSlides) % totalSlides;

    // Translate the carousel
    const carouselImages = document.querySelector('.carousel-images');
    const offset = -currentSlide * 100; // Move by 100% of the width of one slide
    carouselImages.style.transform = `translateX(${offset}%)`;

    // Update active class (optional)
    slides.forEach((slide, index) => {
        slide.classList.toggle('active', index === currentSlide);
    });
}
```

